rdf:Description.dcterms:title: DCMI Namespace for metadata terms in the http://purl.org/dc/terms/ namespace
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: To comment on this schema, please contact dcmifb@dublincore.org.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Title
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: A name given to the resource.
rdf:Description.skos:note: In current practice, this term is used primarily with literal values; however, there are important uses with non-literal values as well. As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is leaving this range unspecified pending an investigation of options.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Creator
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An entity primarily responsible for making the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Examples of a Creator include a person, an organization, or a service. Typically, the name of a Creator should be used to indicate the entity.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Subject
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The topic of the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Typically, the subject will be represented using keywords, key phrases, or classification codes. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. To describe the spatial or temporal topic of the resource, use the Coverage element.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Description
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An account of the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Description may include but is not limited to: an abstract, a table of contents, a graphical representation, or a free-text account of the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Publisher
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An entity responsible for making the resource available.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Examples of a Publisher include a person, an organization, or a service. Typically, the name of a Publisher should be used to indicate the entity.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Contributor
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An entity responsible for making contributions to the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Examples of a Contributor include a person, an organization, or a service. Typically, the name of a Contributor should be used to indicate the entity.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A point or period of time associated with an event in the lifecycle of the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Date may be used to express temporal information at any level of granularity. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as the W3CDTF profile of ISO 8601 [W3CDTF].

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Type
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The nature or genre of the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the DCMI Type Vocabulary [DCMITYPE]. To describe the file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource, use the Format element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Format
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Examples of dimensions include size and duration. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the list of Internet Media Types [MIME].

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Identifier
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An unambiguous reference to the resource within a given context.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Recommended best practice is to identify the resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Source
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: The described resource may be derived from the related resource in whole or in part. Recommended best practice is to identify the related resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Language
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A language of the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as RFC 4646 [RFC4646].

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Relation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Recommended best practice is to identify the related resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Coverage
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The spatial or temporal topic of the resource, the spatial applicability of the resource, or the jurisdiction under which the resource is relevant.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Spatial topic and spatial applicability may be a named place or a location specified by its geographic coordinates. Temporal topic may be a named period, date, or date range. A jurisdiction may be a named administrative entity or a geographic place to which the resource applies. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Thesaurus of Geographic Names [TGN]. Where appropriate, named places or time periods can be used in preference to numeric identifiers such as sets of coordinates or date ranges.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Rights
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Information about rights held in and over the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Typically, rights information includes a statement about various property rights associated with the resource, including intellectual property rights.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Audience
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A class of entity for whom the resource is intended or useful.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Alternative Title
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An alternative name for the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: The distinction between titles and alternative titles is application-specific.
rdf:Description.skos:note: In current practice, this term is used primarily with literal values; however, there are important uses with non-literal values as well. As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is leaving this range unspecified pending an investigation of options.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Table Of Contents
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A list of subunits of the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Abstract
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A summary of the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Created
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of creation of the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Valid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date (often a range) of validity of a resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Available
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date (often a range) that the resource became or will become available.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Issued
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of formal issuance (e.g., publication) of the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Modified
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date on which the resource was changed.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Extent
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The size or duration of the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Medium
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The material or physical carrier of the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Is Version Of
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource of which the described resource is a version, edition, or adaptation.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Changes in version imply substantive changes in content rather than differences in format.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Has Version
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is a version, edition, or adaptation of the described resource.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Is Replaced By
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource that supplants, displaces, or supersedes the described resource.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Replaces
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is supplanted, displaced, or superseded by the described resource.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Is Required By
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource that requires the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Requires
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is required by the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Is Part Of
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource in which the described resource is physically or logically included.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Has Part
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is included either physically or logically in the described resource.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Is Referenced By
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource that references, cites, or otherwise points to the described resource.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: References
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is referenced, cited, or otherwise pointed to by the described resource.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Is Format Of
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is substantially the same as the described resource, but in another format.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Has Format
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is substantially the same as the pre-existing described resource, but in another format.
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Conforms To
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An established standard to which the described resource conforms.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Spatial Coverage
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Spatial characteristics of the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Temporal Coverage
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Temporal characteristics of the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Mediator
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An entity that mediates access to the resource and for whom the resource is intended or useful.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: In an educational context, a mediator might be a parent, teacher, teaching assistant, or care-giver.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Accepted
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of acceptance of the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Examples of resources to which a Date Accepted may be relevant are a thesis (accepted by a university department) or an article (accepted by a journal).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Copyrighted
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of copyright.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Submitted
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of submission of the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Examples of resources to which a Date Submitted may be relevant are a thesis (submitted to a university department) or an article (submitted to a journal).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Audience Education Level
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A class of entity, defined in terms of progression through an educational or training context, for which the described resource is intended.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Access Rights
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Information about who can access the resource or an indication of its security status.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Access Rights may include information regarding access or restrictions based on privacy, security, or other policies.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Bibliographic Citation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A bibliographic reference for the resource.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: License
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A legal document giving official permission to do something with the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Rights Holder
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A person or organization owning or managing rights over the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Provenance
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of the resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: The statement may include a description of any changes successive custodians made to the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Instructional Method
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A process, used to engender knowledge, attitudes and skills, that the described resource is designed to support.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Instructional Method will typically include ways of presenting instructional materials or conducting instructional activities, patterns of learner-to-learner and learner-to-instructor interactions, and mechanisms by which group and individual levels of learning are measured. Instructional methods include all aspects of the instruction and learning processes from planning and implementation through evaluation and feedback.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Accrual Method
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The method by which items are added to a collection.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Accrual Periodicity
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The frequency with which items are added to a collection.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Accrual Policy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The policy governing the addition of items to a collection.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Agent
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A resource that acts or has the power to act.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Examples of Agent include person, organization, and software agent.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Agent Class
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A group of agents.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Examples of Agent Class include groups seen as classes, such as students, women, charities, lecturers.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Bibliographic Resource
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A book, article, or other documentary resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: File Format
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A digital resource format.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Examples include the formats defined by the list of Internet Media Types.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Frequency
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A rate at which something recurs.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Jurisdiction
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The extent or range of judicial, law enforcement, or other authority.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: License Document
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A legal document giving official permission to do something with a Resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Linguistic System
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A system of signs, symbols, sounds, gestures, or rules used in communication.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Examples include written, spoken, sign, and computer languages.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Location
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A spatial region or named place.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Location, Period, or Jurisdiction
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A location, period of time, or jurisdiction.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Media Type
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A file format or physical medium.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Media Type or Extent
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A media type or extent.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Method of Instruction
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A process that is used to engender knowledge, attitudes, and skills.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Method of Accrual
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A method by which resources are added to a collection.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Period of Time
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An interval of time that is named or defined by its start and end dates.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Physical Medium
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A physical material or carrier.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Examples include paper, canvas, or DVD.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Physical Resource
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A material thing.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Policy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A plan or course of action by an authority, intended to influence and determine decisions, actions, and other matters.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Provenance Statement
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of a resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Rights Statement
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A statement about the intellectual property rights (IPR) held in or over a Resource, a legal document giving official permission to do something with a resource, or a statement about access rights.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Size or Duration
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A dimension or extent, or a time taken to play or execute.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Examples include a number of pages, a specification of length, width, and breadth, or a period in hours, minutes, and seconds.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Standard
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A basis for comparison; a reference point against which other things can be evaluated.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ISO 639-2
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The three-letter alphabetic codes listed in ISO639-2 for the representation of names of languages.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: RFC 1766
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of tags, constructed according to RFC 1766, for the identification of languages.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: URI
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of identifiers constructed according to the generic syntax for Uniform Resource Identifiers as specified by the Internet Engineering Task Force.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DCMI Point
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of points in space defined by their geographic coordinates according to the DCMI Point Encoding Scheme.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ISO 3166
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of codes listed in ISO 3166-1 for the representation of names of countries.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DCMI Box
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of regions in space defined by their geographic coordinates according to the DCMI Box Encoding Scheme.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DCMI Period
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of time intervals defined by their limits according to the DCMI Period Encoding Scheme.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: W3C-DTF
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of dates and times constructed according to the W3C Date and Time Formats Specification.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: RFC 3066
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of tags constructed according to RFC 3066 for the identification of languages.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: RFC 3066 has been obsoleted by RFC 4646.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: RFC 4646
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of tags constructed according to RFC 4646 for the identification of languages.
rdf:Description.dcterms:description: RFC 4646 obsoletes RFC 3066.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ISO 639-3
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of three-letter codes listed in ISO 639-3 for the representation of names of languages.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: LCSH
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of labeled concepts specified by the Library of Congress Subject Headings.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: MeSH
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of labeled concepts specified by the Medical Subject Headings.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DDC
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Dewey Decimal Classification.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: LCC
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Library of Congress Classification.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: UDC
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Universal Decimal Classification.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DCMI Type Vocabulary
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of classes specified by the DCMI Type Vocabulary, used to categorize the nature or genre of the resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: IMT
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of media types specified by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: TGN
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of places specified by the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: NLM
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the National Library of Medicine Classification.
